quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  13,6,"They impatiently urge you to bring about evil before good,<sup foot_note=196545>1</sup> while there has already occurred before them similar punishments [to what they demand]. And indeed, your Lord is the possessor of forgiveness for the people despite their wrongdoing, and indeed, your Lord is severe in penalty.",footnotes:196545:1
  13,7,"And those who disbelieved say, "Why has a sign not been sent down to him from his Lord?" You are only a warner, and for every people is a guide."
  13,8,"Allāh knows what every female carries<sup foot_note=196547>1</sup> and what the wombs lose [prematurely] or exceed.<sup foot_note=196546>2</sup> And everything with Him is by due measure.",footnotes:196547:1,footnotes:196546:2
  13,9,"[He is] Knower of the unseen and the witnessed, the Grand, the Exalted."
  13,10,"It is the same [to Him] concerning you whether one conceals [his] speech or publicizes it and whether one is hidden by night or conspicuous [among others] by day."